New equity issuance (i.e., initial public offerings) and secondary offerings (sales of
additional shares by the issuer) add to the supply of stocks. Because issuers tend to
sell new shares when stock prices are thought to be high, increases in issuance of new
shares may often coincide with market peaks.
LOS 13.f: Explain how technical analysts use cycles.
